article.headline: Old Dominion 67, TCU 62
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Isaiah Hunter had 16 points and Alex Loughton added 13 as Old Dominion beat TCU 67-62 on Thursday in the Corpus Christi Caller-Times Challenge. Loughton had 11 rebounds and an assist for Old Dominion (3-0), which took a 37-30 lead into halftime. Hunter was 6-of-14 from the field, including 2-of-6 from 3-point range and hit both of his free throws. He also had three assists. TCU (3-1) was led by Chudi Chinweze with 16 points, while Corey Santee and Marcus Shropshire added 11 apiece.
